  "why": "The paper applies mutations directly to raw input values (image pixel transforms and audio waveform augmentations) via a metamorphic mutation strategy and audio augmentation (speed/volume/filtering/noise) without describing any explicit enforcement of serialized-format constraints (e.g., clipping/rounding to integer pixel ranges or audio sample bounds) that would ensure perturbations survive storage/serialization. The paper does, however, generate some reference audio inputs directly via a TTS engine (serialized audio), but the core test-generation mutations are described as in-memory transformations with no mention of enforcing format constraints—this matches the Metric's 'Medium' case: direct raw-value mutations without explicit format-enforcement.",
